- [alarm beeping]

02:22.034 --> 02:23.620
- Are you kidding me?

02:23.724 --> 02:27.586
- ♪

02:42.896 --> 02:44.379
- Come on, soap man.

02:53.103 --> 02:56.103
I'm gonna miss you,
you slippery son of a bitch.

02:56.206 --> 03:00.310
- ♪

03:00.413 --> 03:03.344
- [buzzer sounds]

03:03.448 --> 03:06.206
- MALE GUARD: Walter Murray,
time to go.

03:06.310 --> 03:09.344
- Oh, already?

03:09.448 --> 03:12.103
I didn't get around
to showering this morning.

03:12.206 --> 03:16.517
- ♪

03:31.724 --> 03:34.000
♪

03:34.103 --> 03:35.620
- Guys!

03:35.724 --> 03:39.000
- ♪

03:39.103 --> 03:40.586
- Over here!

03:40.689 --> 03:43.965
- ♪♪

03:44.068 --> 03:46.482
- [bird cawing]

03:46.586 --> 03:47.896
- He started
digging that dang tunnel

03:48.000 --> 03:49.103
first day we was in there.

03:49.206 --> 03:50.689
- How far did ya make it?

03:50.793 --> 03:53.137
- Like 30 more minutes,
I would have been home free.

03:53.241 --> 03:54.896
- But you're home now.

03:55.000 --> 03:57.310
- It's just not the same.

03:57.413 --> 03:59.241
- Here you go, boys.
Hope you're hungry.

03:59.344 --> 04:00.620
- Oh, are you kidding me?

04:00.724 --> 04:02.241
Half of what
they fed us in there

04:02.344 --> 04:04.068
tasted like wet, rotten cabbage.

04:04.172 --> 04:05.379
- Especially the cabbage.

04:05.482 --> 04:07.827
- You have no idea how
boring it was without you two.

04:07.931 --> 04:10.034
- Mm. It's good to be seen,
little lady.

04:10.137 --> 04:11.034
Well, you know what?

04:11.137 --> 04:12.379
How 'bout we do a
shot to celebrate?

04:12.482 --> 04:13.655
- Alrighty.

04:13.758 --> 04:15.379
- How you like it here, Deb?

04:15.482 --> 04:16.482
- It's cool.

04:16.586 --> 04:17.689
You know, low pressure.

04:17.793 --> 04:19.551
I don't have to take
the work home with me.

04:19.655 --> 04:22.068
- Hey, what about you?
Pour you one.

04:22.172 --> 04:24.413
- Oh, um...

04:24.517 --> 04:26.413
Oh, you know,
I can't drink on the job.

04:26.517 --> 04:29.379
- Well, what in the hell's the
sense in working here, I'd say.

04:29.482 --> 04:30.862
- Maybe to pay the mortgage.

04:30.965 --> 04:32.793
- Well, we all got
our priorities, I reckon.

04:34.241 --> 04:36.206
- Mom, why won't you tell him
the real reason

04:36.310 --> 04:37.448
you're not drinking?
- Sssh.

04:37.551 --> 04:38.931
He just got out.

04:39.034 --> 04:40.241
It's not the right time.

04:40.344 --> 04:41.482
- Okay, when's the right time?

04:41.586 --> 04:42.724
I'm tired of keeping
this a secret.

04:42.827 --> 04:45.448
- You just--
- DOILY: [laughing]

04:45.551 --> 04:47.413
How are my two
favorite parolees, huh?

04:47.517 --> 04:49.103
Fellas, it's been forever.

04:49.206 --> 04:50.551
- We saw you yesterday, Doily.

04:50.655 --> 04:53.068
- Yeah, but you can't hug
through prison bars, huh?

04:53.172 --> 04:55.068
Huh? You can't.
- Not for the lack of trying.

04:55.172 --> 04:58.206
- Best first night out of prison
I can ever remember.

04:58.310 --> 05:01.034
Free beers, fried chicken, whoo.

05:01.137 --> 05:03.068
- Beers aren't free, Vern.

05:03.172 --> 05:04.482
- Well, excuse me, fellas.

05:04.586 --> 05:06.517
- Alright, alright.

05:06.620 --> 05:08.482
Seriously, man,
how long has it been?

05:08.586 --> 05:09.827
- Like 11 hours.

05:09.931 --> 05:11.931
- Nah, come on,
how long's it been?

05:12.034 --> 05:13.241
- Eleven hours.

05:13.344 --> 05:16.620
- Hey, Deb...I just wanted you
to know I'm really sorry

05:16.724 --> 05:18.827
about Ronnie getting killed
in that boat accident.

05:18.931 --> 05:20.793
It's tragic.

05:20.896 --> 05:22.620
If there's anything I can do,
you let me know.

05:22.724 --> 05:24.172
- Well, thank you, Vernon.

05:26.517 --> 05:28.689
Actually, um...there is
something

05:28.793 --> 05:30.758
I wanted to talk to you about.

05:33.758 --> 05:35.793
Ronnie's stuff in the basement,
you know,

05:35.896 --> 05:37.586
I just--I don't know
what to do with it.

05:37.689 --> 05:39.827
- Are you talking about
all that boat crap downstairs?

05:39.931 --> 05:41.551
- It's nautical memorabilia,

05:41.655 --> 05:43.586
you know, so I don't wanna
just throw it out.

05:43.689 --> 05:44.965
Do you know anyone
who might want it?

05:45.068 --> 05:46.655
- I don't know
a whole lot of sailors,

05:46.758 --> 05:48.965
but I guess I can ask around.

05:49.068 --> 05:52.413
- So now that you're a free man,
what's your plan?

05:52.517 --> 05:53.896
Or do you even have one?

05:54.000 --> 05:56.482
- All I know for sure is,
being on the inside

05:56.586 --> 06:00.862
helped me realize...I made
this whole mess.

06:00.965 --> 06:02.620
My career.

06:02.724 --> 06:04.689
Missing out on my little girl
growing up.

06:06.724 --> 06:08.310
I did all that.

06:08.413 --> 06:10.793
I did it to myself.

06:10.896 --> 06:12.448
[sighs]

06:12.551 --> 06:15.103
Now I just wanna get back
to the real me.

06:15.206 --> 06:16.482
My music.

06:16.586 --> 06:18.758
Even if it means
living in my car.

06:18.862 --> 06:20.241
- I think that's great.

06:20.344 --> 06:21.551
- You do?

06:21.655 --> 06:25.034
- Yes, Vern, I've always
been a fan of your music.

06:25.137 --> 06:26.862
You don't have to sleep
in your car.

06:26.965 --> 06:30.344
Alright, just stay
in the basement.

06:30.448 --> 06:32.586
This is strictly platonic.

06:32.689 --> 06:33.827
- Well, wait a minute now.

06:33.931 --> 06:37.103
Uh, platonic doesn't mean
we can't fool around

06:37.206 --> 06:38.379
now and again, does it?

06:38.482 --> 06:40.241
- That's exactly
what platonic means.

06:40.344 --> 06:42.758
- Looks like table three's
almost ready for their check.

06:42.862 --> 06:45.551
Do you mind settling up with
them and locking up tonight?

06:45.655 --> 06:46.551
- Oh, yeah, yeah, no problem.

06:46.655 --> 06:47.862
- Thanks.

06:47.965 --> 06:49.862
My sitter just sent me a picture
of a bite mark

06:49.965 --> 06:51.448
courtesy of my four-year-old.

06:51.551 --> 06:52.448
- This is Vern.

06:52.551 --> 06:53.448
Vern this is Kaitlyn.

06:53.551 --> 06:54.724
She owns the bar.

06:54.827 --> 06:55.862
- Pleasure to meet you, Ma'am.

06:55.965 --> 06:58.241
- The pleasure's all yours.

06:58.344 --> 06:59.931
I've heard stories.

07:00.034 --> 07:01.827
Thanks, Debbie.

07:01.931 --> 07:04.310
- Good to know my reputation
is still intact.

07:04.413 --> 07:05.586
- You reap what you sow.

07:05.689 --> 07:07.206
- Oh, look
who's the preacher now.

07:07.310 --> 07:09.068
- If you can do it,
apparently anyone can.

07:09.172 --> 07:12.620
- Uh, look at us bantering on
like an old married couple.

07:12.724 --> 07:13.965
Next thing you know,
we'll be arguing over

07:14.068 --> 07:16.172
which side of the bed
to sleep on.

07:16.275 --> 07:17.551
- Not gonna happen, Vern.

07:17.655 --> 07:18.551
You're in the basement...

07:18.655 --> 07:20.103
on a cot.

07:20.206 --> 07:21.655
- Hey, check it out.

07:21.758 --> 07:23.827
Who wants a free game of pool?

07:25.517 --> 07:27.034
- I got a better idea.

07:27.137 --> 07:30.310
- ♪

07:34.275 --> 07:36.655
♪ Drop it down low,
make the rooster crow ♪

07:36.758 --> 07:38.827
♪ Stand there, tattooed,
doing her thing ♪

07:38.931 --> 07:41.172
♪ Driving me wild,
like I'm going insane ♪

07:41.275 --> 07:43.655
♪ It won't take much,
'bout three or four drinks ♪

07:43.758 --> 07:46.137
♪ She can get loose,
not worry 'bout shame ♪

07:46.241 --> 07:48.620
♪ Drop it to the flat line,
rattle that cage ♪

07:48.724 --> 07:50.827
♪ Them boys at the bar
messing round, get rage ♪

07:50.931 --> 07:53.206
♪ Try moving in fast,
she tell ya get going ♪

07:53.310 --> 07:55.793
♪ Girl is shaking that ass
to her favorite song ♪

07:55.896 --> 07:57.517
