07:57.620 --> 07:59.137
♪ Drop, drop drop

07:59.241 --> 08:04.241
♪ Drop, drop drop drop,
drop, drop drop, drop ♪

08:04.344 --> 08:05.758
♪ Drop it down low low

08:05.862 --> 08:10.413
♪ Drop, drop drop
drop, drop drop drop ♪♪

08:10.517 --> 08:12.896
- [rooster crows]

08:20.551 --> 08:22.586
- Hell's far.

08:22.689 --> 08:24.758
Look like somebody
had a damn party.

08:31.758 --> 08:33.862
What the hell?

08:40.034 --> 08:42.379
Hey, Deb, look what I found.

08:42.482 --> 08:44.379
- BOTH: Morning, Vernon.

08:47.965 --> 08:49.241
- Sheri and I were--
- Sheila.

08:49.344 --> 08:52.448
- Sheila and I were just
bonding over our taste in men.

08:52.551 --> 08:55.000
- Yeah. Debbie suggested perhaps
I shouldn't sleep

08:55.103 --> 08:58.551
in stranger's basements
with men twice my age

08:58.655 --> 09:00.137
who live in basements.

09:00.241 --> 09:02.137
- Sounds like
pretty solid advice.

09:03.275 --> 09:04.206
- Hi, honey.

09:04.310 --> 09:06.413
Um, this is
your dad's friend Sheila.

09:06.517 --> 09:09.310
She just stopped by
for an early breakfast.

09:09.413 --> 09:10.724
- Okay, mom, please.

09:10.827 --> 09:12.000
Vernon, gross.

09:12.103 --> 09:13.206
And no offense, Sheila.

09:13.310 --> 09:14.275
- None taken.

09:14.379 --> 09:17.344
You know what?
I'm actually late, so--

09:17.448 --> 09:19.620
- [phone dings]
- Look, that's my ride.

09:19.724 --> 09:20.724
Thanks for the coffee.

09:20.827 --> 09:22.241
- Yeah, it's nice meeting you.

09:22.344 --> 09:25.379
- VERNON: You can just leave
the shirt at the door there.

09:25.482 --> 09:27.344
- [indistinct whispering]

09:27.448 --> 09:29.103
- Please tell me
she's at least in college.

09:29.206 --> 09:31.034
- She's working her way
through law school.

09:31.137 --> 09:32.724
- You'd think she'd be
a little bit smarter.

09:32.827 --> 09:35.000
[indistinct whispering]

09:35.103 --> 09:36.931
- [whispers] Stop.

09:37.034 --> 09:38.827
Have you figured out
what to do with Ronnie's stuff?

09:38.931 --> 09:41.482
- Well, I believe
this may have some answers.

09:41.586 --> 09:42.655
- Where did you find this?

09:42.758 --> 09:44.862
- Well, I was organizing
Ronnie's stuff,

09:44.965 --> 09:45.793
and came across it.

09:45.896 --> 09:46.758
You ever seen it?

09:46.862 --> 09:48.241
- I didn't even know about it.

09:49.827 --> 09:51.068
Where are we gonna
play this thing?

09:51.172 --> 09:52.206
- 1985.

09:52.310 --> 09:53.689
- [laughs] Yeah.

09:53.793 --> 09:55.517
I mean, who even
has VCRs anymore?

09:55.620 --> 09:57.068
- [doorbell rings]

09:57.172 --> 09:59.172
- Now, do you want VHS or BETA?

09:59.275 --> 10:01.517
Because depending on the year
the tape was made and its size,

10:01.620 --> 10:05.206
either format could be
applicable to these recorder.

10:05.310 --> 10:07.172
Okay.

10:12.482 --> 10:14.896
- If you are watching this,
it's probably

10:15.000 --> 10:16.793
because some tragedy
has befallen me,

10:16.896 --> 10:18.655
and the nation mourns for me.

10:18.758 --> 10:22.137
The time has come for ol' Ronnie
to shed this beautifully toned

10:22.241 --> 10:24.827
mortal coil and move
into the great beyond.

10:24.931 --> 10:27.344
The great adventure
at sea in the sky.

10:27.448 --> 10:28.517
- [static buzzes]

10:28.620 --> 10:31.620
- First, my mortal remains will
be cast atop

10:31.724 --> 10:33.310
a gilded vessel such as such

10:33.413 --> 10:36.344
while a choir
of Valhalla's Knights

10:36.448 --> 10:38.758
sings my praises
with timeless classics

10:38.862 --> 10:40.586
from badass
martial arts' movies.

10:40.689 --> 10:45.413
A lone archer will let loose
a single arrow--[shoooo]--

10:45.517 --> 10:48.551
catching the pyre
and my mortal remains ablaze.

10:48.655 --> 10:49.758
Ow.

10:49.862 --> 10:51.310
- He does not look Nordic at
all.

10:51.413 --> 10:52.206
- He's Scots Irish.

10:52.310 --> 10:53.206
- Um...

10:53.310 --> 10:54.862
- Maybe he's just joking around.

10:54.965 --> 10:57.758
- Just to be clear,
this is not a joke.

10:57.862 --> 10:59.517
Failure to service
these requests will result

10:59.620 --> 11:05.206
in a nonstop haunting by me,
Ronnie, forever, ever--

11:05.310 --> 11:07.137
- Well, I don't want
a Ronnie poltergeist.

11:07.241 --> 11:09.172
- But there's no way
I can pull all this off.

11:09.275 --> 11:10.827
- RONNIE: --ever--
- Now let's not get

11:10.931 --> 11:12.482
our collective panties
in a wad here.

11:12.586 --> 11:15.241
I'll go downstairs and see if I
can find a sequel to this thing.

11:19.482 --> 11:21.310
- MAN: My boy, my boy.

11:21.413 --> 11:24.413
Debbie got us living down here
in a Ronnie junkyard.

11:24.517 --> 11:27.034
I feel like
I'm caught in a trap.

11:27.137 --> 11:28.965
I can't walk out without getting
some of Ronnie's [bleep]

11:29.068 --> 11:30.482
on my blue suede shoes.

11:30.586 --> 11:31.758
- You got that right.

11:31.862 --> 11:33.344
- MAN: I got an idea for you,
son.

11:33.448 --> 11:36.206
Ronford wants a floating
funeral, what better way

11:36.310 --> 11:38.310
to get rid of him
and his memory than put him

11:38.413 --> 11:41.793
on a float of fire and get rid
of all this nautical crap.

11:41.896 --> 11:43.310
- I think I catch our drift.

11:51.275 --> 11:53.172
Hey, good news and bad news!

11:53.275 --> 11:55.448
Bad news is I didn't find
another tape.

11:55.551 --> 11:58.896
The good news is, all we gotta
do is work together as a team,

11:59.000 --> 12:00.965
divide up the task,
and we can do this.

12:01.068 --> 12:02.689
- Really?
- Yes.

12:02.793 --> 12:03.862
I mean, I'll be charge

12:03.965 --> 12:05.896
of the floating funeral
boat fire deal.

12:06.000 --> 12:08.896
I can load up
all of Ronnie's stuff.

12:09.000 --> 12:11.517
And, Walt, I bet
you know stuff about Viking.

12:11.620 --> 12:14.551
- Well, I mean, I'm no expert,
but I studied a little bit on.

12:14.655 --> 12:15.862
- Come on, what do you say?

12:15.965 --> 12:17.206
Let's do this!

12:17.310 --> 12:18.965
Come on, we can do.
- Really?

12:19.068 --> 12:21.379
- Everybody! Together now!

12:21.482 --> 12:22.758
- [whip lashes]

12:22.862 --> 12:25.137
- Doily, how'd you get in here?

12:25.241 --> 12:27.068
- You guys leave your windows
unlocked at night.

12:27.172 --> 12:28.896
That's not a good idea,
it's dangerous.

12:29.000 --> 12:30.793
Anyway, one, two, three!

12:30.896 --> 12:32.413
Family!

12:32.517 --> 12:33.827
Family!

12:33.931 --> 12:35.724
Family!

12:37.344 --> 12:39.241
Family.

12:39.344 --> 12:40.793
- Did you come in
through a window?

12:40.896 --> 12:42.344
- Yeah, bedroom window, yeah.

12:45.172 --> 12:47.517
- I think you should
really stick with Mom.

12:47.620 --> 12:50.310
- Hey, Deb, why don't you
ride with me?

12:50.413 --> 12:51.862
- Go for it. I can drive.

12:53.103 --> 12:55.620
- Come on, it'll be fun.

12:55.724 --> 12:57.275
- Does it smell
like stripper in your car?

12:57.379 --> 12:58.862
- Uh, just a little bit.

12:58.965 --> 13:00.620
- Am I gonna get
glitter on my ass?

13:00.724 --> 13:02.000
- Let's hope so.

13:02.103 --> 13:03.793
Here, let me get
the door for you, my lady.

13:05.034 --> 13:06.000
Here you go.

13:06.103 --> 13:08.137
What's first on your list there?

13:08.241 --> 13:09.862
Uh, great.

13:14.241 --> 13:17.517
I just never understood spending
a bunch of money on a fancy box

13:17.620 --> 13:19.724
just to drop it in a dirt hole.

13:19.827 --> 13:21.965
- I think it's nice to show
appreciation for someone

13:22.068 --> 13:23.310
when they're gone.

13:23.413 --> 13:25.793
- I think it's nice to show
appreciation for someone

13:25.896 --> 13:27.137
while they're still here.

13:27.241 --> 13:28.793
- [door creaks]

13:28.896 --> 13:30.965
- Vernon, look, I need
to talk to you about something.

13:31.068 --> 13:32.448
- Well, hey, folks,
can I help ya?

13:32.551 --> 13:34.517
- Hey, Haus, these things
sure ain't cheap, are they?

13:34.620 --> 13:37.344
- Oh, trust me, sir, we receive
them at wholesale prices,

13:37.448 --> 13:40.379
and there's very little markup.

13:40.482 --> 13:41.551
- This one looks nice.

13:41.655 --> 13:43.206
- This is
our top-of-the-line model

13:43.310 --> 13:45.137
with all the bells and whistles.

13:45.241 --> 13:46.448
- That thing got cup holders.

13:46.551 --> 13:48.551
- Yeah, my father
recently passed away

13:48.655 --> 13:50.172
and took two tall boys with 'im.

13:50.275 --> 13:51.862
- Oh, I'm so sorry.

13:51.965 --> 13:53.034
Was he sick?

13:53.137 --> 13:55.413
- Actually, he was
the picture of health.

13:55.517 --> 13:58.034
We was on a family camping trip.

13:58.137 --> 13:59.896
And he was involved
in a bear attack.

14:00.000 --> 14:01.206
- Whoa!
- Oh my God.

14:01.310 --> 14:04.655
- [crying]

14:04.758 --> 14:07.275
- Um, I'm sorry, sir,
how much is this one?

14:07.379 --> 14:09.000
- Question for you.

14:09.103 --> 14:12.517
Would you buy a new car without
taking it for a test drive?

14:12.620 --> 14:13.827
- No.

14:13.931 --> 14:18.724
- And yet you will not
spend eternity in your car.

